# echo &amp;quot;speedstep_centrino&amp;quot; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; &amp;#x2F;etc&amp;#x2F;modules&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then, install the “powernowd” daemon:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-area&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;line-numbers language-bash&#34; data-language=&#34;bash&#34; data-start=&#34;1&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34;&gt;# apt-get install powernowd&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Powenowd’s default settings should be OK for most people.&lt;/p&gt;
